         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">22/9/77. ¶  ¶ I redeem my promise dear Dr Haig, to dedicate to you as a permanent mark of respect a new plant. It came from the western part of the great bight. ¶  The specimen of this new everlasting...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">77.09.22a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Haig</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS is accompanied by an official 'On Her Majesty's Service | <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>GOVERNMENT BOTANIST, Melbourne' envelope addressed to 'Dr Haig, J. P. &amp;c <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Emerald Hill.</hi>
                     </seg>'</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Helipterum Haigii</seg> is enclosed with the letter, with one of M's specimen labels: 'Helipterum Haigii F.v.M. Near Port Eucla. Richards.' The collector was almost certainly Police Trooper Thomas Richards of Fowler's Bay, SA, who collected many specimens for M near Eucla in 1877.</p>
               </note>22/9/77.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I redeem my promise dear Dr Haig, to dedicate to you as a permanent mark of respect a new plant. It came from the western part of the great bight.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Great Australian Bight.</p>
               </note> The specimen of this new everlasting is a poor one, but the species is pretty and well worthy of your honored name.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">In publishing <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Helipterum Haigii</seg> in B77.10.02, p. 107, M described Haig as 'amico … studiorum meorum fautori benignissimo' [a most benign friend and supporter of my studies].</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
